Strong directional lighting illuminates the scene, casting prominent shadows. The light source appears to be from the upper right, causing the shadows to fall to the lower left of the raised edges and within the groove itself, particularly along the left and bottom edges of the carved lines. This creates a strong sense of depth and texture.

The background is the consistent, finely textured granular surface, which appears relatively flat apart from the drawn letter. The color palette is dominated by muted tones of gray, beige, and darker gray for the shadows. The entire image is focused on the drawn letter and the texture of the medium it's created in.
